{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_81","type":"agent_message","text":"The JRT support flag fixed the compiler bootstrap; the remaining failures are now real library metadata problems. Spring’s parser is reflectively calling `com.sun.source` APIs, and its fallback path is masking the original reflection miss by throwing `NoSuchFieldException` on `delegate`. I’m enumerating the reflective calls in `fieldvalues.javac` now so I can register the exact methods/fields it needs."}}
